HEADWORD: Knife switch
<hw>Knife switch</hw>. <fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>A switch consisting of
one or more knifelike pieces hinged at one end and making contact near
the other with flat gripping springs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

